 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/12/02 2:59:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uitchibumbashalots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ItchibumBashalots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 5:26:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beware Coran &amp; Shadowan</span><hr size=1> Ok so where is Haegan slamming you for posting this....<br><br>Let me guess... its because its not me.<br><br>Thanks for the heads up Bjond.<br><br>Ichi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 5:58:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beware Coran &amp; Shadowan</span><hr size=1> yeh, it's pretty GHEY. reporting someone for killing a level 6 mob should get you drowned in boiling oil. I think you should just give up EQ because it doesn't get any better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 7:32:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   If there was no TLC ..</span><hr size=1> .. I'd agree with Heagan.  I'd agree so much that I wouldn't even have been there until after I had both Idol and Code and I certainly wouldn't have sent my druid.  Unfortunately, TLC on the ribs starts at level 10, they're part of the monk epic, and they're moderately rare (takes about 4H to get 3 ribs on average if uncamped).  You *have* to camp them when either you are 9 or when your alternate is 9; ie. TLC makes for more contested camps.<br><br>At level 9, language is a serious barrier as well.  I had Bjond translate, so I was lucky enough to learn that they were:<br><br>1. oh, we were just saving your friend, she almost died! (uh, she was at full hp/mana when you took the putrids)<br>2. we're on a quest, we're not doing anything wrong! (uh, so questing gives you letters of marque to KS?)<br>3. guide ordered them to desist, then invis'd, then caught 'em doing it again.<br>4. guide ordered them to alternate and they took that to mean they got all the putrids that weren't attacking me and could KS every other one that was.<br><br>They also went on and on about twinks -- wanted the guide to ban me for twinking and such.  I didn't catch much of that, only the guide's responses really, but those were pretty funny.  Guide warned them for obscene language several times -- wish my slave had enough human to let me see what they said there, too.  The guide said something like, &quot;claiming to RP is no excuse for such harrasment&quot;.<br><br>The bad part about this area is that the putrids only spawn at dawn and dusk.  That's roughly a 45 minute wait for a chance to observe a KS, so the guide couldn't hang out and babysit and catch them again after her alternate declaration.  I got them on another KS with a /report, but by the time a guide responded, I had given up on it long ago. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uitchibumbashalots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ItchibumBashalots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 7:33:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beware Coran &amp; Shadowan</span><hr size=1> There he is...must be gettin slow keepin up with all these posts defending himself.<br><br>Ichi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrittyeye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>grittyeye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 8:49:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Beware Coran &amp; Shadowan</span><hr size=1> What bothers me with the attitude of &quot;It's only a low level quest/mob&quot; is if they aren't shown there are consequences for actions in the low levels, what's it going to be like when they get to the high levels and they KS that named rare spawn or whatever all you high level mucky-mucks go after? <br><br>People will be throwing a fit and rightly so, but what makes you think they are going to have some kind of radar telling them at what level it isn't appropriate to steal anymore? Do you think they are just going to say to themselves &quot;Oh, we've reached level 55, we're not going to be asses anymore, no sir, we've developed morals&quot;? No, they're not. These two guys are just an example, but it goes for anyone who displays the type of attitude they have displayed. A complete inability to be respectful of others.<br><br>Why is the focus on what level the mob in question was? The focus should be on the attitude displayed when they are confronted. Did they continue to KS you after talking to them? Did they intentionally train you as repayment for confronting them? Did they then verbally harrass you?<br><br>If the answers are &quot;yes&quot;, well, then it doesn't matter what level it happened at, because if they are doing it at level 9 without repercusions, then they will be doing it at level 55 too, and I don't think anyone wants that. Granted, I've never reported anyone, luckily have never been in the situation to need to, but I just don't feel like there should be some free pass to be an ass until you reach higher levels.<br> <p>Narie<br>The Bumbling Half Elf Druid<br>Now debuting in her 24th season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/02 10:59:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  language plays a role in some of this.</span><hr size=1> Not in Bjonds case as he interpreted. But I also have sat at that spawn and been ks'd by a then red to me cleric who was helping a then blue to me monk through it.   <br><br>It is hard to set up some sort of sharing agreement without common languages, for alot of camps until people realize they actually have to learn languages.<br><br>Many times I have broken a camp and then had someone set up and start pulling from it.  They are in their rights due to PnP, but it is not good player form.  I usually just leave and come back in 20-30 min to find their corpse.   <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Excellent Tailor <br>Master Baker <br>Lousy Smith <br>Master Brewer <br>Master  Drunk <br>Aspiring Polyglot <br>Wannabe Alchemist <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/02 11:26:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: language plays a role in some of this.</span><hr size=1> The rules are actually quite clear on this point.<br><br>Kill-stealing is a violation of the Play Nice Policies, and it *DOES NOT MATTER* what level the monster being stolen is.<br><br>Early on, on this server, KSing seemed to be de rigeur, and I /petitioned plenty of people.  I don't see many of those people around anymore.  At all.  I'd gladly do it again.<br><br>Naria's right.  If they're doing it at level 9, they're not going to stop by level 55 if no one tells them to stop.<br><br>Lasgalen Lothir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/02 11:32:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: language plays a role in some of this.</span><hr size=1> Well, there is a difference between KS.. You pull a mob, then red to you cleric kills it in one nuke.  This is not only rude but against the rules.<br><br>And camp infringement.. where someone starts pulling from the same pool of mobs without saying a word. Not a problem if we are talking the aviak city in SK, but is a problem if you are talking an Aviak guard spawn in lake rathe.<br><br>Infringement is not per se against PnP, its just rude and won't make you many friends.  According to VI there are no camps.  We the players invented those. <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Excellent Tailor <br>Master Baker <br>Lousy Smith <br>Master Brewer <br>Master  Drunk <br>Aspiring Polyglot <br>Wannabe Alchemist <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/02 9:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: language plays a role in some of this.</span><hr size=1> omg someone said pnp. rofl.<br><br>pnp, albeit deters grief players, is the single WORST thing to invoke.<br><br>a_newb_64 : I am going to tell! pnp says you are being a bad person!<br>a_newb_64 has lost points toward ever being considered cool again! (2)<br><br>by the time you are petitioning gm's for pnp, you may as well just delete. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/02 10:55:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beware Coran &amp; Shadowan</span><hr size=1> So once again a certain someone IGNORES the fact that KS'ing is KS'ing no matter the level of the mob. Ignores the comments about not learning what is and isnt acceptable behavior unless told, forced or taught that information.<br><br>Once again, slowly<br><br><br>A    person    that   Kill steals    at  low level      and     is   never     confronted        or corrected       will       still     be    Kill stealing       at        55.<br><br><br>It isnt the level of the mob, nor the level of the player that makes KS'ing. It is the action of attacking and stealing a kill from someone already engaged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=351.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=351.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=351.topic